adjectives.description: bounderish (comparative more bounderish, superlative most bounderish)

entries.meaning: Pertaining to or having the characteristics of a bounder; loutish; boorish.
examples: In Powell's war, only the rotters flourish—notably Kenneth Widmerpool, whose humorless egomania and bounderish one-upmanship have won him critical status as one of the great comic creations of modern English fiction.
